Arno Botha of the Vodacom Bulls during the United Rugby Championship 2021/22 match between the Bulls and Sharks. BackpagePix/Willem Loock JOHANNESBURG - The Bulls look set to lose the services of Arno Botha. The loose forward is looking to make a European move. Botha has been linked with a move to French Top14 club Lyon. His contract with the Tshwane side he joined in 2020 from MunsterÂ will end on 1 July. This after leaving the Bulls in 2018. Botha made his debut for the union back in 2011 and played for seven years in Pretoria before first moving overseas. The 30-year-old won two Springbok caps between 2012 and 2013.